  "question": "<p>1. Did the Federal Communications Act create a new, individual right of broadcast access for the Carter-Mondale Presidential Committee, as the representatives of a candidate for federal office?</p>\n<p>2. Did the act authorize the Federal Communications Commission to determine the beginning of the 1980 presidential campaign for purposes of the act and to assess the specific broadcast needs of the CMPC?</p>\n<p>3. Did CBS have the right to decline to sell thirty minutes of broadcast time to the CMPC under the First Amendment?</p>\n",
